creator: Dora Sigerson Shorter
description: LibriVox volunteers bring you 8 recordings of The Priest's Brother by Dora Sigerson Shorter. This was the Fortnightly Poetry project for October 18, 2105. Read in English by ALMcClain; bsdarby; Christie Crews; David Lawrence; Newgatenovelist; J. McDougall; Leonard Wilson and Vanessa Garcia. An early Hallowe'en offering. Dora Maria Sigerson Shorter was an Irish poet and sculptor, who after her marriage in 1895 wrote under the name Dora Sigerson Shorter. She was born in Dublin, Ireland, the daughter of George Sigerson, a surgeon and writer, and Hester (née Varian), also a writer. She was a major figure of the Irish Literary Revival, publishing many collections of poetry from 1893. Her friends included Katharine Tynan, Rose Kavanagh and Alice Furlong, writers and poets. (Summary from Wikipedia) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org.
